9 "§5.11. Water fluoridation program
10 A. The secretary of the Louisiana Department of Health shall establish in the office
11 of public health a fluoridation program for the purpose of protecting the dental health of the
12 citizens of this state, and especially children, through the prevention of tooth decay.
13 B.(1) Each public water system that has at least five thousand service connections
14 and natural levels of fluoride that are outside the optimal range established in the rules and
15 regulations adopted pursuant to this Section shall acquire, install, operate and maintain
16 appropriate equipment and material in order to maintain the level of fluoride in its water
17 system in the optimal range for the purpose of protecting the dental health of citizens of this
18 state, as established in the rules and regulations adopted pursuant to this Section.
19 (2) Each public water system with at least five thousand service connections that has
20 fluoride levels outside the optimal range established in the rules and regulations adopted
21 pursuant to this Section shall provide to the Louisiana Department of Health no later than
22 March 1, 2009, an estimate of the total capital costs to acquire and install fluoridation
23 treatment equipment capable of maintaining fluoride levels within the optimal range for the
24 purpose of protecting the dental health of citizens of this state, as established in the rules and
25 regulations adopted pursuant to this Section.
26 (3) No public water system shall be required to comply with Paragraph (1) of this
27 Subsection unless sufficient funds have been identified by the state, whether by
28 appropriation, capital outlay, grants or similar means or source of funds, as available to that
29 system for the cost of acquiring and installing fluoridation equipment and the cost of
30 material required to fluoridate said system for at least six months from the date of initial
31 installation.
32 (4) A public water system that has never used fluoridation to adjust fluoride levels
33 in its water and whose water contains fluoride in amounts outside the range established in
34 the rules and regulations adopted pursuant to this Section as optimal for the purpose of
35 protecting the dental health of the citizenry shall be exempt from compliance with Paragraph
36 (1) of this Subsection provided all of the following apply:
37 (a) A petition requesting the exemption has been signed by at least fifteen percent
38 of the registered voters who reside in the precincts served by said water system, as certified
39 by the parish registrar of voters, and has been presented to the governing authority of each
40 municipality or parish in whose jurisdiction the system provides service.
41 (b)(a) A local election has been called on the exemption after the petition has been
42 received by each governing authority pursuant to Subparagraph (a) of this Paragraph.
43 Participation in the election shall be limited to those precincts in which the water system
44 provides service. The local election shall be called and conducted by the governing authority
45 of each municipality in whose jurisdiction the water system provides service if all of the
46 registered voters served by the water system reside wholly within the jurisdiction of one or
47 more municipalities. However, the local election shall instead be called and conducted by
48 the governing authority of each parish in whose jurisdiction the water system provides
49 service if either of the following applies:
